---
import Layout from "../../components/Layout.astro";
import Hero from "../../components/Hero.astro";
import CTASection from "../../components/CTASection.astro";
---

<Layout title="Moose's Rescue Story" description="Moose's rescue story, from a dog meat farm in Busan to safety, trust, and a new life.">
  <Hero
    eyebrow="Rescue Stories"
    title="Moose's Rescue Story"
    text="From a dog meat farm in Busan to safety, trust, and a new life."
    primaryLabel="Donate"
    primaryHref="/donate/"
    secondaryLabel="Volunteer"
    secondaryHref="/volunteer/"
    tertiaryLabel="More Stories"
    tertiaryHref="/rescue-stories/"
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container story-shell">
      <article class="story-article">
        <p class="eyebrow">Moose</p>
        <h2>From Survival To Safety.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Moose is a Tosa Inu, a rare Japanese mastiff breed known for strength, loyalty, and presence. Before he became the quiet, watchful dog he is today, Moose was one of hundreds of dogs trapped in the dog meat trade in South Korea.
        </p>

        <section class="story-section">
          <h3>Rescued In Busan</h3>
          <p>
            In October 2024, K9 Global Rescue helped take part in a major rescue operation in Busan, South Korea, where approximately 580 dogs were saved from a dog meat farm. Moose was one of them.
          </p>
          <p>
            He had been living in the kind of environment no animal should ever experience: confined, vulnerable, and facing an uncertain future in a trade built on suffering.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="story-section">
          <h3>The Road To Safety</h3>
          <p>
            After the rescue, Moose and the other dogs were moved to safety at a sanctuary in South Korea, where the long process of recovery, care, and placement began.
          </p>
          <p>
            Moose became one of the first dogs from that rescue to travel to the United States. He was flown from Seoul to Los Angeles, beginning a new chapter far from the cages and fear he had known.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="story-section">
          <h3>Learning Safety</h3>
          <p>
            Moose's journey did not end when he landed in America. Like many dogs rescued from trauma, he needed time, patience, structure, and care.
          </p>
          <p>
            He was nursed back to health and slowly began learning what safety felt like. Over time, his real personality started to show.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="story-section">
          <h3>A New Life</h3>
          <p>
            Today, Moose is quiet, watchful, loyal, and deeply bonded to the people he trusts. He carries himself with the seriousness of a guardian, but underneath that strength is a gentle and thoughtful dog who was given the second chance he deserved.
          </p>
          <p>
            Moose now lives a life of safety, love, routine, and dignity. His past will always be part of his story, but it no longer defines his future.
          </p>
        </section>

        <blockquote>
          "Saving one dog will not change the world, but for that one dog the world will change forever."
        </blockquote>

        <p class="closing-note">
          Moose's story reflects K9 Global Rescue's mission to help animals in crisis move toward care, safety, and the chance to live without fear.
        </p>
      </article>
      <aside class="story-side" aria-label="Moose story photos">
        <figure class="story-photo primary-photo">
          <img src="/assets/moose-portrait-story.jpg" alt="Moose wearing a blue collar after rescue and recovery." loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <figcaption>Moose after rescue and recovery.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="story-photo">
          <img src="/assets/moose-arrival-story.jpg" alt="Moose standing in a Los Angeles parking garage after arriving from Incheon, South Korea." loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <figcaption>Moose on the day he landed in Los Angeles from Incheon, South Korea.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    title="Support Rescue Work Like Moose's."
    text="Help K9 Global Rescue support animals in crisis through rescue coordination, medical care, transport, and trusted partner work."
    primaryLabel="Donate"
    primaryHref="/donate/"
    secondaryLabel="Volunteer"
    secondaryHref="/volunteer/"
    tertiaryLabel="More Stories"
    tertiaryHref="/rescue-stories/"
  />
</Layout>

<style>
  .story-shell {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(260px, 340px);
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .story-article {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .story-article h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-ivory);
  }

  .story-article .lead {
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }

  .story-section {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.35rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(232, 180, 72, 0.22);
  }

  .story-section h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .story-section p,
  .closing-note {
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: 1.04rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  blockquote {
    margin: 2rem 0 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.35rem 1.5rem;
    border-left: 5px solid var(--color-gold);
    background: #090a07;
    color: var(--color-ivory);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  .story-side {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-content: start;
  }

  .story-photo {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 320px;
  }

  .story-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232, 180, 72, 0.24);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .primary-photo img {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    object-position: center 18%;
  }

  .story-photo:not(.primary-photo) img {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    object-position: center 45%;
  }

  .story-photo figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .story-shell {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .story-side {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      align-items: start;
    }
  }
</style>
